name: Doug McMillon
bio: Husband. Father. Razorback. Gadget geek. Retail lifer. Proud Walmart associate.

social_posts.post_text: The books I read this year cover a variety of topics, but I kept returning to those that look to the future and ask: How can we all work together to make it better? It’s an important topic to think about and directly aligns with our company’s purpose. We exist to help people save money and live better. Each and every associate can make a positive difference in our communities – it’s worth our time and effort.

Walmart Academies help our company stand out from the crowd – like a fun holiday sweater! They also help us change for the better, creating new opportunities for associates to grow, while sharing our culture and values with the next generation of leaders. I was happy to meet with the team late last week and appreciate the work they are doing to help promote a culture of learning. Thanks also to Alesha and Grant for the one-of-a-kind sweater.

Had a great day with some of our associates in Atlanta, yesterday. Our teams in Store 3261, Store 3775 and Sam’s Club 6643 are focused on serving our customers and members during these busy weeks leading up to Christmas. Thank you all!

We’re so proud to support Wreaths Across America for a 15th year. This week, with the support of 40 Distribution Centers, 100 Walmart drivers will transport 100,000 wreaths to ceremonies around the U.S. I’m happy we’re able to give back to our communities in this way, and honor those who gave all.
null

Had such a great time visiting with our teams at Store 3418 in Wesley Chapel, FL, as well as Stores 3526, 1213, and Sam’s Club 4818 in Brooksville this week. It’s easy to get caught up in their enthusiasm for the new year ahead! They are ready to go with Valentine’s Day and spring merchandise for customers and members. Special thanks to our leaders, Alejandra, Kamilla, Tom and Scott. Thanks also to Phyllis and the bakery team at 3526 and Chandra and the health care team at 3418. Way to go!

This week’s Manager Academy is comprised of a great group of @walmart, @samsclub and supply chain leaders from around the country. They are here to discuss our business including our values, culture and servant leadership. I enjoyed visiting with you all!
Thank you to Renardo and the team at Store 2280 in Mountain View, CA! It was fun to visit this week and see the great job you’re doing serving our customers and community. Keep it up!

Today in “The Morning Meeting,” we discussed aspects of our company that we love and will stay committed to like our purpose, values, servant leadership and the fact that our associates make the difference. Then we looked ahead at some of the exciting changes we’re planning to better serve our customers and members. We like driving change. We loved having Steuart, Alice and Lynne Walton as well as alum Rollin Ford and Susan Chambers join us and share their thoughts. It was also special to celebrate long-term service awards. Together, this group of 52 represents 1,445 years with the company and so many powerful stories. Congratulations!

Our team in Store 2649 in Irving, TX, is ready for football and Valentine’s Day. Thank you to Raul and the team for visiting with us today. I appreciate the work you’re doing to serve our customers. Proud of you all!

This group of associates from our stores and distribution centers are completing a 10-week program for recent college grads where they work in home office roles in something like an internal internship. Very cool. It’s also exciting to see 17 of the 20 associates completed their degrees through the Live Better U program – way to go you all! Enjoyed visiting with you.

Wow, what a job you did finishing off last year and getting us started for this one! You’ve put us in a strong position and created momentum. It’s impressive. We’ve got a tremendous opportunity in front of us as we work together to save people money and help them live better in more ways. Let’s remember to thank them and invite them back. I’m proud of what you’re accomplishing, and I hope you are, too. Nice job!

Claude Harris, our company’s first merchant, passed away this weekend surrounded by his loving family. Without Claude, and the strong foundation he built, Walmart would not be the company it is today. 
 
The service mindset Claude helped create at Walmart lives on in every merchant who has followed in his footsteps, and in associates around the world. He was a champion of fairness, transparency and honesty. We’re still operating with the principles Claude helped us learn.
 
Please join me in remembering Claude and appreciating him and his family for their impact on this purpose-driven company he helped build.

It was good to visit with associates in Katy, TX, this week. Wally, Lynn, and the team at Store 768 have worked to grow their pickup and delivery service and serve customers in new ways. You can really see the pride they have in their store. Robert at Store 3226 started as a cashier and is now leading the team there. And Sam’s Club 4764 is setting high standards through their member-obsessed culture. Proud of you all!

There’s a lot happening in San Antonio this week. It’s @samsclub’s 40th birthday and I enjoyed visiting with everyone in town during a fun and inspiring celebration at the Sam’s Club Year Beginning Meeting. Not to be outdone, the local @walmart stores look good! Thanks to Jeff, Rosalia and team at Store 2404.

Appreciate the productive and enjoyable conversation with these store managers today! We had lots of tenure in this group, including Glenn, who in 1988 worked in our very first Supercenter in Washington, MO. I’m grateful to work with so many people with such valuable experience and wisdom.

Each spring, the Walmart U.S. Year Beginning Meeting is an opportunity for us to get things kicked off the right way: Dedicating ourselves to better serving our customers and associates. This year, we talked about ways we can turn it up another notch. I’m really proud to see we’re moving forward with speed, bringing forward new ideas and products to meet the needs our customers and associates. Let’s go!

I’m really proud of the associates at Sam’s Club 8221 in Harvey, LA and Walmart 1163 in New Orleans. Thank you for taking great care of our members and customers, and congratulations to Vanessa, who is retiring this week after 17 years with the company. Great job!

@samsclub is celebrating 40 years of making members’ lives better. To highlight the milestone, Jackie and Miriam from Club 4774 and Jim from Club 6428 rang the bell at the @nyse along with Kath McLay and the leadership team. Thank you, and congratulations! Here’s to many more.

Had a great day yesterday meeting associates at Store 5664 in Camarillo, CA, and Store 2032 in Oxnard, CA! A special shoutout to Liz in Camarillo for her work on pickup and delivery. In Oxnard, several regular customers praised associates Willy and Adrienne for their cheerful service. Great job, everyone, and thank you!

The Morning Meeting today was awesome. More than 230 long-term service associates joined us from across the nation, representing over 8,400 years with the company. Their stories of service and of going above and beyond for our customers show our people make the difference.
 
In the meeting we focused on our efforts across our business to become a regenerative company, where we do more than conserve - we restore, renew and replenish. Rob Walton joined us on stage to share more about how our journey started. He reminded us that no other company can make the kind of impact we can when we all work together. To celebrate Rob’s role in our sustainability journey, we announced “Rob’s Trail,” which will be a central part of the trail system on our new Home Office campus.

Associates at Store 2812 in Rochester, MN, are ready for spring! I really appreciate Mitch and the team. They are working hard to make sure customers find what they need and have a great experience. They know a friendly face can make all the difference. Way to go!

Associates, congratulations on a strong quarter! You’re delivering on our purpose, helping customers and members save money and live better however they choose to shop with us.
 
Associates and Shareholders Week is just around the corner. I’m looking forward to seeing many of you in person!

This morning at Store 100, here in Bentonville, AR, associates from around the world helped ring the opening bell of the @NYSE. I appreciate Jose from Distribution Center 6020 in Brooksville, FL, for officially ringing us in, and the associates at Store 100 for hosting the event. Great job! Thank you also to Lynn Martin, President of the NYSE, for joining us. #WMT2023

Associates visiting the Home Office during Associates Week bring an unmatched level of energy and enthusiasm - the conversations, smiles and laughs make it feel like a family reunion. Spending time with you all makes it one of my favorite times of the year! #wmt2023

At today’s Associate Celebration, we heard amazing stories of associates who made the impossible… possible. We all have this power. Every day, we can make a huge impact in a customer or member’s life. Everything we have achieved in our company’s history – every impossible thing – was because of you, our associates, working together to live out our purpose and values. 
 
Thank you to everyone who attended today. I know you’ll keep making the difference. You'll keep making the impossible... possible!

Alycia and the team at Store 1841 in Chesapeake, VA, recently welcomed customers back after a very challenging time for our associates and the community. I’m so proud of their resilience and am inspired by their ability to come together as a team – making what seems impossible, possible.
 
Sam’s Club 6368, also in Chesapeake, VA, is looking great and serving members with excellence. Thank you to Brittany and the entire team there. At nearby Store 5253, Candice, Andrew and the TLE crew are working hard to make sure our customers get the service they need, with a smile. Thank you, all!

During last week’s Associate Celebration, we recognized Fernande Dubé-Deschênes who works at Store 3035 in Granby, Quebéc, Canada, and has an incredible 59 years of service! Fernande is our longest serving associate.
 
Fernande started at Woolworth, which eventually became Walmart Canada. We’re grateful she’s chosen to work with us and serve her customers so well for so long. Merci beaucoup!

Oramis, who works at @samsclub 4712 in Houston, TX, just celebrated his 8th anniversary with the company. During Associates week we were proud to celebrate his promotion, along with his hard work and leadership, as he and his team continue to thrive. Keep up the great work!

Just wrapped up two great days with Gonzalo Gebara and the Walmart Canada team, visiting Stores 1089 and 3013 and PDC 6080 in Calgary, Alberta, Canada.
 
We met so many engaged and excited associates, including long-serving and award-winning associates like Salim. It was good to see Market Leader Amrit who I got to help promote to Store Manager 10 years ago. This time we promoted Tanvir to Store Manager of Store 1049 in Strathmore, Alberta. I also appreciate Store Managers Aisan and Corey, who are running great omnichannel stores.
 
The trip was capped by a fantastic visit to PDC 6080, twice winner of the Canadian DC of the Year award. I was really impressed by the team’s commitment to regeneration and the compelling life and career stories of many of their associates, including Jason, Ronaldo, Cheikh, Curtis, Ann and Mariana. It was also good to visit with the Women In Retail and Women In Supply Chain roundtables. 
 
It was great to be back in Canada and I’m already looking forward to my next visit!

At The Morning Meeting last week, we welcomed about 400 associates from around the country, each of which have over 20 years of service – some with many, many more. Together they represented 8,205 years of experience. When we say we’re “People-powered,” this is what it’s all about. Thank you to these associates for joining us. I appreciate you!
The Interns v. Executives softball game is a fun tradition that goes back decades. This year the Execs got the W, with a decisive 18-5 victory. Thank you, interns, for spending your summer with us!

A group of 15 Associate-to-Driver Fleet facilitators were in Bentonville this past week to strengthen the skills they need to help develop our newest drivers. Their training also has a strong and important emphasis on the role they play as culture keepers for our associates.

So far, more than 190 associates have graduated from the 12-week Associate-to-Driver program these facilitators help enable. This includes our largest class yet, 72 associates, who finished just last week. Graduates can finish with a CDL license and become members of the Walmart Private Fleet.

Even more associates will begin their training next week, and you can be sure this group will be ready to help. Great job!

This week a group of us had the opportunity to visit stores and our team in Santiago, Chile. There were lots of highlights including recognizing and promoting associates like Jeremy and Sandra. I’m so proud of how this team has worked together to serve our customers and our communities. Viva Chile!

Associates, congratulations on another strong quarter! I’m really proud of the way we’re working together to help each other and serve our customers and members. Each of us is part of a big, global team that shares the same purpose: Every day, we’re helping people around the world save money and live better. They are counting on us to deliver where and how they want to be served. Let’s be sure to greet them, practice the 10-foot rule and thank them for their business. I appreciate you. Let’s keep this momentum going into the holiday season.

I really enjoyed spending time with our @walmart and @samsclub managers and merchants at this week’s Holiday Meetings. There’s a lot of fun merchandise coming your way very soon and I think our customers and members are going to love it.

While we were in Houston, we had a fantastic visit with Oriana and her team at Store 5612. They are ready for Back to College and Labor Day. They are in stock and their seasonal features look great. Standing tall!

It was good to visit with marketplace sellers this week during our first-ever Marketplace Seller Summit. There is an ecosystem here that unlocks unmatched opportunity and I’m glad they’re on the journey, reimagining retail alongside us. I also had a wonderful time visiting with Candace, Tabarri, Chase, and many others at Store 1584 in Las Vegas. I appreciate their commitment to serving our customers.

We’re ready for the holidays! Earlier this week, we visited our team at Store 2139 in Lynn, MA, with associates Lenny, Adama and Store Manager Juanri, as well as Store 3114 in Saugus, MA, with Store Manager Shannon. Halloween and Christmas are looking good.
 
It was fun to see Eleanor again at Store 2139. She was recognized during our Associates Week celebration back in 2022, and still dresses up each day to bring joy to our customers.
 
Thank you all!

Store 3159 in Teterboro, NJ, is newly remodeled, and the team has it looking fantastic! I enjoyed visiting with Russ, Giovanna, Meryem, Mabel, Jose and all our associates there who are working to make the holidays special for our customers. Great job!

Friday, we welcomed over 150 long-term service associates to the Home Office for the Morning Meeting and celebrated their stories, legacy and combined 5,241 years of service. 

Nohemi, who is celebrating 35 years and works at @samsclub 8126 in Brownsville, TX, had an especially powerful story. She told us about the time she met Helen Walton at the 1993 Shareholders Meeting. Nohemi still remembers Helen’s humility and ability to make every associate feel seen and appreciated.
 
Thank you to all our associates for helping each other and serving the customers and members who need us. You keep our culture of strong teams and relationships going!

Today’s conversation with @paramountco CEO, Bob Bakish, and Global Head of Inclusion, Marva Smalls, was a great discussion on the power of listening, learning and growing as a team. People are the core of our business, and there’s no question we’re better when everyone is included and heard. We appreciate Bob and the Paramount team for visiting Bentonville and the Home Office and for their continued partnership with Walmart. 

Associates, let’s keep working together to build a culture of belonging and making a difference in our communities around the world. We have a shared mission, common purpose and values that help us work to be our best, wherever we are.

A huge thank you to all of the veterans working in our business and shopping with us. We’re thankful for you and your families. Today, Marine Corps Sergeant (Ret.) and founder of The War Horse, Thomas Brennan visited our home office and shared information about their work. Thank you to them and also to associates Mike Morales Jr. and Jerry Wherry for their work driving volunteer efforts in the San Antonio area. Way to go!
 
We’re grateful for the sacrifice our country’s veterans and their families make in service to our country. It’s a privilege to support them while they are in uniform and as they transition to civilian life. Over the past decade, we have hired more than 500,000 veterans and military spouses and hope even more choose to build their careers here at Walmart. Thank you all.

Associates, thank you for your hard work and dedication to living our purpose and values. You make the difference, helping millions of people around the world save money and live better lives.
 
As we begin the holiday season, let’s continue to be good merchants and operators, and put our customers and members at the center. This is our opportunity to do what we do best – deliver convenience and value.
 
I appreciate you, and I’m proud to work alongside you. Let’s keep it up.

Thank you to our associates around the world working hard to serve our customers and members this busy holiday season. Yesterday, I visited with several teams in Texas, including a new Food DC and eComm FC in Lancaster, along with our store in Grapevine and a @samsclub in Dallas. Josh, Ervin, John, Jessica, Renata and their teams are an inspiration and source of positive energy.
 
During the visit they asked me what my favorite Thanksgiving dish was. There’s no doubt it’s my wife’s chocolate pecan pie – I’ve been looking forward to it for weeks now! Happy Holidays, everyone!

Thank you to the awesome teams at Bodega Aurrera, Walmart and Sam’s Club Mexico for their hospitality this week. It was a lot of fun visiting associates in the Mexico City area. They’re working with a common purpose, serving our customers and members with the right assortment at the right price, however they choose to shop with us. Way to go!

Friday, we celebrated 262 associates from around the country and welcomed them to the Home Office for the Morning Meeting. Together, they have a combined 8,745 years of experience.
 
Margaret from Store 72 in Pittsburg, KS, is celebrating an incredible 50 years of service and shared with us her story of meeting our founder, Sam Walton. Jill started as a seasonal associate 35 years ago in Farmington, MO, and showed us the dollar bill Sam signed for her when he was visiting her store.
 
Associates like Margaret and Jill help us carry our culture forward, sharing our purpose and values with newer associates, customers and members. Thank you, all!
Lots of variety in the books I’m sharing for this year. There’s so much to learn about emerging technology, but I still love reading @walmart stories and books about heart, culture and service.

Yesterday I had the chance to visit Store Manager Russ and our team at Store 3473 in Las Vegas. The store is looking good and I’m so proud of them! Teresa, especially, is a strong apparel merchant and really knows her stuff. Nice job!
Husband. Father. Razorback. Gadget geek. Retail lifer. Proud Walmart associate.
